issue_comments.body:
@haosdent  What do you think about the usage difference. Earlier at the call site it used to be:
interface->foo(arg1, arg2);

With this change, the interface would be:
dispatcher.dispatch(&interface::foo, arg1, arg2);

commit_comments.body:
@westurner IIRC the architecture images were 404s beforehand even with an absolute URL because the files didn't live there. There were few images that were actually working beforehand, most images were broken. The previous comment to this one (260acd03b45c9a203a53bc92171aedadbb970dad) in the PR actually fixed the script so the deployment would post-process the markdown as it did with links. There is still something going wrong with the deployment (i.e. manual running of the script and getting committed to subversion).

I've mentioned in a couple of mailing list threads that we need to make this process automated via the Jenkins server. @davelester was helping to organise this with the Apache ops guys as he is the web site maintainer.

Here is the JIRA issue: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MESOS-3687

